<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,151,573]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,404,429]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Comments:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[345,584,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Clusiidae" genus="Allometopon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eotoxon">
<emphasis box="[345,584,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Allometopon eotoxon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is allied to 
<taxonomicName box="[717,899,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Clusiidae" genus="Allometopon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hesperotoxon">
<emphasis box="[717,899,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">A. hesperotoxon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[914,1072,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 100 – 106" captionStartId="87.[151,264,1823,1846]" captionTargetBox="[172,1415,193,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@87.[172,1416,193,1803]" captionTargetPageId="87" captionText="FIGURES 100 – 106. Allometopon hesperotoxon spec. nov.; 100: female, photo, dorsal; 101: holotype, photo, dorsal; 102: same, lateral; 103: female, photo, lateral; 104: paratype, external genitalia, left lateral; 105: same, posterior; 106: internal genitalia, left lateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258785/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
Figs 
<number box="[972,1072,404,428]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="100101.0">100, 101</number>
</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName box="[1136,1315,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Clusiidae" genus="Allometopon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="machaeroges">
<emphasis box="[1136,1315,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">A. machaeroges</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1332,1428,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 157 – 161" captionStartId="96.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@96.[151,1436,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="96" captionText="FIGURES 157 – 161. Allometopon machaeroges spec. nov., holotype; 157: photo, dorsal; 158: same, lateral; 159: external genitalia, left lateral; 160: same, posterior; 161: internal genitalia, left lateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258794/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
Fig. 
<number box="[1385,1428,404,429]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="157.0">157</number>
</figureCitation>
) (see comments for 
<taxonomicName box="[367,548,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Clusiidae" genus="Allometopon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hesperotoxon">
<emphasis box="[367,548,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">A. hesperotoxon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), but can be differentiated on the basis of an absence of a medial stripe on the frons and a dorsal stripe on the male first flagellomere (stripe vestigial to absent in 
<taxonomicName box="[1118,1301,476,501]" class="Insecta" family="Clusiidae" genus="Allometopon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hesperotoxon">
<emphasis box="[1118,1301,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">A. hesperotoxon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
males), the palpus and pleuron are entirely pale, the paraphallus is broader and membranous, and the distiphallus and hypandrial setae are longer.
</paragraph>
